definition.value: A  pyrazolone  that is 1,2-dihydro-3H-pyrazol-3-one substituted by a dimethylamino group at position 4, methyl groups at positions 1 and 5 and a phenyl group at position 2. It exhibits analgesic, anti-inflammatory, and antipyretic properties.
A 2,6-diaminopimelic acid in which both chiral centres have S configuration. It is a component of bacterial cell wall.
